    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "Write mercy and truth upon the tablet of your heart\u2014Trust in the Lord\u2014Honor Him with your substance\u2014Whom the Lord loves He corrects\u2014Happy is the man who finds wisdom.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "My son, forget not my law; but let thine heart keep my commandments:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 5:33.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Peace of God.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let not mercy and truth forsake thee: bind them about thy neck; write them upon the table of thine heart:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Truth.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 6:8 (4\u201310).",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Cor. 3:3 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heart.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So shalt thou find favour and good understanding in the sight of God and man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 2:26.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Trust in the Lord with all thine heart; and lean not unto thine own understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith; Trust in God; Trustworthiness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Heart.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust Not in the Arm of Flesh.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 67
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Intelligence; Understanding.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guidance, Divine; Problem-Solving.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not wise in thine own eyes: fear the Lord, and depart from evil.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 15:21; 28:15.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It shall be health to thy navel, and marrow to thy bones.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Health; Word of Wisdom.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Honour the Lord with thy substance, and with the firstfruits of all thine increase:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honor.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Tithing.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 22:29.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So shall thy barns be filled with plenty, and thy presses shall burst out with new wine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abundant Life; Blessing.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord; neither be weary of his correction:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For whom the Lord loveth he correcteth; even as a father the son in whom he delighteth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 15:3.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Happy is the man that findeth wisdom, and the man that getteth understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Study; Understanding.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the merchandise of it is better than the merchandise of silver, and the gain thereof than fine gold.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "She is more precious than rubies: and all the things thou canst desire are not to be compared unto her.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 8:18 (12\u201318).",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is every one that retaineth her.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 7:12.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord by wisdom hath founded the earth; by understanding hath he established the heavens.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 4:1.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 7:11.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My son, let not them depart from thine eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So shall they be life unto thy soul, and grace to thy neck.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 1:9.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou liest down, thou shalt not be afraid: yea, thou shalt lie down, and thy sleep shall be sweet.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the desolation of the wicked, when it cometh.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Lord shall be thy confidence, and shall keep thy foot from being taken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 4:6; Alma 7:27 (26\u201327). TG\u00a0Dependability.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of thine hand to do it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:26 (25\u201326); Luke 6:30.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 6:10 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Say not unto thy neighbour, Go, and come again, and to morrow I will give; when thou hast it by thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Devise not evil against thy neighbour, seeing he dwelleth securely by thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:27.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 21:10.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Strive not with a man without cause, if he have done thee no harm.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 25:8; Rom. 12:18 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Envy thou not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Oppression.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the froward is abomination to the Lord: but his secret is with the righteous.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0perverse.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The curse of the Lord is in the house of the wicked: but he blesseth the habitation of the just.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Surely he scorneth the scorners: but he giveth grace unto the lowly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0humble.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 67
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wisdom.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}